@Node "Introduction"

 @{u}1. Introduction@{uu}

    This library offers functions to manipulate ARexx macros trees.

    A child is an ARexx macro, run via RxChild() function and
    referred by an integer ID.

    When a child is launched, it exists till the end of the parent
    macro or till it is freed via RxChildFree() function.

    The status of a child is one of
        o RUN
        o SUSP
        o END

    When a child is not in the END status, you can manipulate its
    vars env via RxChildGetVar() RxChildSetVar().

    When a child is in the END status, you can only get its result
    via RxChildResult() function.
@EndNode

